Hey all,

my roommates and I are working on an app/website for a marketplace product, and while we have some of the backend and the iOS app largely built, we're looking for help on making a beta of our Android app. We're willing to pay for the development as well. We're looking for anyone with prior experience in Android dev, and preferably with experience in Firebase and Stripe dev kits. If you're interested, drop me an email at neelbaronia@berkeley.edu with maybe a couple examples of apps you've built/published, and I'll get back to you more on what we need specifically.

Thanks
history.subject: Looking to get help on an Android app, willing to pay
